// Build configuration for the PoseDeck app.
//
// API_BASE_URL is the base URL of the PocketBase backend. It is surfaced into
// Info.plist (key `APIBaseURL` via $(API_BASE_URL)) and read at runtime by
// AppConfig.apiBaseURL.
//
// NOTE: xcconfig treats `//` as a comment everywhere, including inside values.
// A bare `http://localhost:8090` would have everything from the `//` stripped,
// yielding `http:`. Work around this by splitting the scheme's slashes into a
// separate variable and recombining — a standard xcconfig idiom.
SLASH = /
// Default = localhost so the simulator + agent XCUITest verification works out
// of the box against a same-machine `pocketbase serve` (this is the DEFAULT the
// build ships with). This is only the build-time default; the user can now
// point the app at any backend from the sign-in screen's "Use a different
// server" field (item 4), which persists and rebuilds the API stack — no
// rebuild needed for on-device or TrueNAS testing.
API_BASE_URL = http:$(SLASH)$(SLASH)localhost:8090

// On-device LAN testing alternative: build with the dev Mac's LAN IP baked in
// (phone + Mac on one Wi-Fi). Either enter it on the login screen at runtime
// (preferred), or override this at build time, e.g.:
//   xcodebuild ... 'API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.68.55:8090'
// See docs/ON_DEVICE_TESTING.md.
